{
  "text": "Nonetheless, blocking EGFR with a neutralizing antibody caused the marked accumulation of TGF-α, not AR, in the cell culture supernatant (Supplementary Fig. 2 ), indicating that TGF-α is rapidly bound by EGFR and utilized by the cells in the absence of the antibody due to its higher affinity for EGFR relative to AR [CITATION_1] . Moreover, combinations of antibodies against AR, TGF-α and HB-EGF suppressed MUC5AC expression more strongly than an AR-neutralizing antibody alone. This combinatorial effect might again indicate that more than one EGFR ligand contributes to the complex cell response to WSPM2.5.",
